-------------------------------
- JacORB Notification Service -
-------------------------------

if you're using a JDK < 1.4 you'll need 
to download the library gnu.regexp from 
http://www.cacas.org/java/gnu/regexp
and make it available in the classpath

to start the Notification Service run bin/ntfy or bin/ntfy.bat.

ntfy[.bat] [-printIOR] [-printCorbaloc] [-writeIOR <filename>] 
           [-port <oaPort>] [-channels <channels>] [-help]
	
The script starts a EventChannelFactory

* -printIOR: 		print the IOR to STDOUT

* -printCorbaloc: 	print the Corbaloc to STDOUT

* -writeIOR <filename>: write the IOR to a file

* -port <oaport>:	try to start the service on a specific port

* -channels <channels>:	create a number of EventChannels


any comments/suggestions to the JacORB Developer Mailing List

mailto:jacorb-developer@lists.spline.inf.fu-berlin.de or visit
http://lists.spline.inf.fu-berlin.de/mailman/listinfo/jacorb-developer

Alphonse Bendt

